    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Safety Commission was responsible for following developments in safety in coal mines, including safety regulations made by the public authorities, and for assembling the necessary information on progress made and practical results obtained, particularly in the field of accident prevention. The Safety Commission made use of the information in its possession in order to submit proposals to the Governments for the improvement of safety in coal mines."@en;
